content.htmlText: This lovely neighborhood, known as "Selvia" for the ancient tree treated as a landmark in the area, is a great mix of bustling and peaceful. You'll find several cafes located immediately downstairs, and an array of excellent restaurants and bars at the Galeria around the corner on Rruga Qemal Stafa. Two of Tirana's most noteworthy tourist attractions, Skenderbeg Square and Pazar i Ri, are each located about a five minute walk away. Don't miss the chance to pick up some delicious seasonal fruits and vegetables or traditional Albanian handicrafts at Pazar i Ri, or to have a cold beer and a fresh-grilled kebab at one of the many pubs lining the Pazar. About seven minutes away you'll find Toptani Center, a luxury mall featuring five floors of retail shopping and an outpost of the international grocery chain Conad. Right next to Toptani a cobble-stoned restaurant-lined pedestrian avenue leads to the National Theatre, the main Boulevard, and the Bllok.

Don't miss the chance to pick up some delicious seasonal fruits and vegetables or traditional Albanian handicrafts at Pazar i Ri, or to have a cold beer and a fresh-grilled kebab at one of the many pubs lining the Pazar. About seven minutes away you'll find Toptani Center, a luxury mall featuring five floors of retail shopping and an outpost of the international grocery chain Conad. Right next to Toptani a cobble-stoned restaurant-lined pedestrian avenue leads to the National Theatre, the main Boulevard, and the Bllok.

Tirana is an incredibly pedestrian-friendly city, full of cafes, restaurants, boulevards, and attractions. We highly recommend getting out and exploring the city on foot. One pleasant route is to walk west from the apartment to Skenderbeg Square -- which should take about five minutes -- and then to head south through the Square, past the great mounted statue of the national hero Skenderbeg, and down the boulevard to the enormous oasis at the heart of the city, Parku i Madh. If you're in the mood for a stroll walk around the lake (Liqeni) in the middle of the park, then head west once you come back out on the Boulevard to check out the vibrant nightlife of the Bllok.

section.about: Hello and welcome to Albania! I am a retired diplomat who worked in the Albanian foreign service for more than 22 years. Due to the nature of my work I have travelled all over the world and seen some beautiful places. Throughout the years I’ve always enjoyed those trips where my wife and I stayed in rented flats instead of hotels - we’ve found it’s a much more interesting way to get a flavor for a new city! We hope you will enjoy our space and all Tirana has to offer!

htmlDescription.htmlText:
Sun-drenched spacious two-bedroom apartment, just minutes from Skenderbeg Square, Pazar i Ri, and countless cafes and restaurants. This quiet south-facing apartment is located on the 8th floor of a new apartment building in the heart of Tirana. Light streams in a wall of windows and two balconies to illuminate a sizable master bedroom suite with its own bathroom, an open plan living room + dining room + full kitchen, and a guest bedroom with access to a second bathroom.

The space
Each bedroom offers a queen size bed which can comfortably sleep two. The kitchen is equipped with a full set of pots and pans, dishware, and cutlery. The apartment also features a utility room with washing machine, clothes drying racks, and iron. The apartment has excellent WiFi.

reviews.comments:
Thanks you Saimir,
Everything was perfect !

Saimir hat schnell auf die Fragen geantwortet
Er war sehr nett und hilfsbereit und hat uns gezeigt wo man hingehen kann.

reviews.comments:
The host was kind enough to wait for us in front of the apartment.
The house was in a very good location and was only 12 euros from the airport by taxi.
The living room and two bedrooms were very spacious and very comfortable for our family of four.
The refrigerator, TV, and washing machine were brand new and easy to use.
Communication was great, if you asked the host something, he would respond within a minute.
One of the most amazing Airbnb’s I’ve stayed at, and one of the most generous hosts I’ve met, it was a perfect stay for us.

Saimir è un ottimo padrone di casa, è stato puntuale e più che disponibile in tutto, nelle indicazioni per visitare luoghi,  per andare a mangiare e altro.... il nostro volo era ben oltre l'orario di check out ma lui ci ha permesso di restare ... addirittura ci ha prenotato il taxi per andare in aereoporto.  Sicuramente lo consiglio per chiunque voglia visitare Tirana la posizione dell'appartamento è veramente molto strategica.

localizedReview.comments: Saimir is a great landlord, he was punctual and more than available in everything, in the directions to visit places,  to go to eat and more... our flight was well past check-out time but he allowed us to stay ... he even booked us the taxi to go to the airport.  I definitely recommend it for anyone who wants to visit Tirana. The location of the apartment is really very strategic.

reviews.comments: Saimir è super gentile e disponibile! La casa si trova in pieno centro e tutto è facilmente raggiungibile a piedi. Se dovessi tornare a Tirana sicuramente scegliere di nuovo questo alloggio!

localizedReview.comments: Saimir is super kind and helpful! The house is in the heart of downtown and everything is easily accessible on foot. If I had to go back to Tirana, definitely choose this place again!

reviews.comments: Everything was fine during our ten days stay. Being close to the center and walking distance to everywhere is great. When you have a problem, there is owner who reaches you immediately for a solution. You won't regret your stay.

Grazie mille per averci ospitate, Saimir.
Casa molto spaziosa, centralissima, a pochi minuti di passeggiata da Piazza Skanderbeg. Saimir è stato gentilissimo e ci ha pure consigliato degli ottimi posti dove andare a mangiare.
Ci torneremo

localizedReview.comments:
Thank you so much for hosting us, Saimir.
Very spacious, very central house within walking distance of Skanderbeg Square. Saimir was very kind and also recommended great places to eat.
We'll be back

reviews.comments:
Saimir was really helpful!
Each time we needed an information, he was really fast in explaining us the things we had to know!
older place but spacious and super convenient in terms of location. Everything you want and need is mere steps away. The balconies are great and the showers have good pressure.

I haven't stayed in many Air bnb's, but this one was absolutely perfect. The owner was super helpful and urgently responsive. He personally greeted us with the keys and a tour of the house even though we arrived in the middle of the night. Then he personally sought us off and even helped to secure our taxi and to insure we didn't get lost or ripped off.
Thank you again Saimir, for the great stay and the recommendations for everything.
AWESOME, communication, location, vibe and experience. Truly a lovely stay. Good Wifi, Fantastic location and stellar communication from start to finish. What a great place to visit.
AMAZING! Perfect location. Attentive. Accommodating. Comfortable! Such. Great place!!!!! Wow!!!!!!?
Incredible kindness, helpfulness, and hospitality.  We could not have asked for more. Honestly. Such a wonderful host. Lovely apartment. Ease with regards to all logistics.THANKYOU!

It is a very nice, clean, comfortable apartment with a lot of space and it seemed to me as if nothing was missing there.  I felt at home.  In the kitchen room I find everything you just need to have the ingredients and you can cook whatever you want.  Then stand on the balcony and look out over the city.
